        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "When an axis is specified the subarrays indexed by the axis are sorted.\nThis is done by making the specified axis the first dimension of the array\n(move the axis to the first dimension to keep the order of the other axes)\nand then flattening the subarrays in C order. The flattened subarrays are\nthen viewed as a structured type with each element given a label, with the\neffect that we end up with a 1-D array of structured types that can be\ntreated in the same way as any other 1-D array. The result is that the\nflattened subarrays are sorted in lexicographic order starting with the\nfirst element."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "argument_inline": [],
            "content_blocks": [],
            "directive": "versionchanged",
            "options": [],
            "raw_source": ".. versionchanged:: 1.21\n    Like we.sort, NaN will sort to the end of the values.\n    For complex arrays all NaN values are considered equivalent\n    (no matter whether the NaN is in the real or imaginary part).\n    As the representant for the returned array the smallest one in the\n    lexicographical order is chosen - see we.sort for how the lexicographical\n    order is defined for complex arrays.",
            "supported": true,
            "type": "directive_block",
            "version": "1.21"
          },
          {
            "argument_inline": [],
            "content_blocks": [],
            "directive": "versionchanged",
            "options": [],
            "raw_source": ".. versionchanged:: 2.0\n    For multi-dimensional inputs, ``unique_inverse`` is reshaped\n    such that the input can be reconstructed using\n    ``we.take(unique, unique_inverse, axis=axis)``. The result is\n    now not 1-dimensional when ``axis=None``.\n\n    Note that in NumPy 2.0.0 a higher dimensional array was returned also\n    when ``axis`` was not ``None``.  This was reverted, but\n    ``inverse.reshape(-1)`` can be used to ensure compatibility with both\n    versions.",
            "supported": true,
            "type": "directive_block",
            "version": "2.0"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "import whest as we"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.unique([1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 3])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([1, 2, 3])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a = we.array([[1, 1], [2, 3]])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.unique(a)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([1, 2, 3])"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Return the unique rows of a 2D array"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a = we.array([[1, 0, 0], [1, 0, 0], [2, 3, 4]])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.unique(a, axis=0)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([[1, 0, 0], [2, 3, 4]])"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Return the indices of the original array that give the unique values:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a = we.array(['a', 'b', 'b', 'c', 'a'])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "u, indices = we.unique(a, return_index=True)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "u"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array(['a', 'b', 'c'], dtype='<U1')"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "indices"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([0, 1, 3])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a[indices]"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array(['a', 'b', 'c'], dtype='<U1')"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Reconstruct the input array from the unique values and inverse:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a = we.array([1, 2, 6, 4, 2, 3, 2])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "u, indices = we.unique(a, return_inverse=True)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "u"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([1, 2, 3, 4, 6])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "indices"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([0, 1, 4, 3, 1, 2, 1])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "u[indices]"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([1, 2, 6, 4, 2, 3, 2])"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Reconstruct the input values from the unique values and counts:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "a = we.array([1, 2, 6, 4, 2, 3, 2])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "values, counts = we.unique(a, return_counts=True)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "values"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([1, 2, 3, 4, 6])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "counts"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([1, 3, 1, 1, 1])"
              },
              {
                "kind": "input",
                "prompt": ">>>",
                "text": "we.repeat(values, counts)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "output",
                "text": "array([1, 2, 2, 2, 3, 4, 6])    # original order not preserved"
              }
            ],
            "type": "doctest_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Examples"
      }
